colors (laughs) all right.

00:02:01.293 --> 00:02:05.133
If this radius is length r,

00:02:05.133 --> 00:02:09.600
then the length, if this
angle is two radians,

00:02:09.600 --> 00:02:12.833
then the arc that
subtends it is going to be

00:02:12.833 --> 00:02:17.600
two radiuses long, so this
length right over here,

00:02:17.600 --> 00:02:20.333
is two radiuses.

00:02:20.333 --> 00:02:23.700
Now, what fraction of the
entire circumference is that?

00:02:23.700 --> 00:02:26.134
Well, the entire circumference, we know,

00:02:26.134 --> 00:02:27.400
we know this from basic geometry,

00:02:27.400 --> 00:02:31.233
the entire circumference
is two pi times the radius,

00:02:31.233 --> 00:02:34.800
or you can say it's two pi
radii, two pi "radiuseses",

00:02:34.800 --> 00:02:36.700
(laughs) two pi radii is
the correct way to say it.

00:02:36.700 --> 00:02:38.233
So, what fraction is it?

00:02:38.233 --> 00:02:41.800
It's two radii, it's two radii,

00:02:41.800 --> 00:02:46.800
over two pi radii, over two pi radii,

00:02:47.068 --> 00:02:51.666
twos cancel out, rs cancel
out, and so it is one "pith",

00:02:51.666 --> 00:02:53.172
(laughs) I guess you could say,

00:02:53.172 --> 00:02:57.172
it is one over pi of
the total circumference.

